The paper deals with computational complexity in the context of voting rules, which is a topic that falls under the category of Game Theory (cs.GT). The use of partial preferences and the focus on manipulation and bribery suggest that Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Data Structures (cs.DS) may also be relevant sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of algorithms, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
